  <summary date="2019-08-20T21:35:16Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Fair Elections Now Act

This bill establishes the Fair Elections Fund, which shall provide funding to Senate candidates who meet&#160;specified conditions and agree to abide by certain requirements, such as limits on types of campaign funding sources and a minimum number of appearances in&#160;public debates. The bill also (1) revises provisions related to broadcasts of Senate campaign advertisements, (2) provides a tax credit for individuals who make certain types of Senate campaign contributions, and (3) imposes a tax on certain U.S. government contracts.</summary>
